            <title>[SUREFIRE-642] TestNG support doesn&apos;t w/o Junit on classpath</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SUREFIRE-642</link>
                <project id="12317927" key="SUREFIRE">Maven Surefire (Moved to GitHub Issues)</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I have the same problem that Larry reported here:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;http://jira.codehaus.org/browse/SUREFIRE-615?focusedCommentId=232600&amp;amp;page=com.atlassian.jira.plugin.system.issuetabpanels%3Acomment-tabpanel#action_232600&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://jira.codehaus.org/browse/SUREFIRE-615?focusedCommentId=232600&amp;amp;page=com.atlassian.jira.plugin.system.issuetabpanels%3Acomment-tabpanel#action_232600&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Our company excludes junit from classpath to make sure people won&apos;t use it by mistake.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
